1. Define a small family tree using male, female, and parent facts.

2. Write rules to determine:

○ father(X, Y): X is the father of Y.

○ mother(X, Y): X is the mother of Y.

○ grandparent(X, Y): X is the parent of a parent of Y.

% --- FACTS ---

male(bob). 
male(tom).
male(jim).
female(pam).
female(liz).
female(ann). 
% parent(Parent, Child).

parent(bob, liz).
parent(bob, tom).
parent(pam, liz). 
 parent(tom, ann).
 parent(tom, jim). 
 
 % --- RULES --- 
 % X is a father if X is a parent AND X is male.
 father(X, Y) :- parent(X, Y), male(X).
 % X is a mother if X is a parent AND X is female. 
 mother(X, Y) :-
 parent(X, Y),
female(X).
